# WHAT IT IS
#   The btcsuite project is the canonical Go reimplementation
#   of the Bitcoin Core protocol stack ‚Äî `btcd` is the
#   full-node daemon, `btcwallet` is the wallet daemon, and
#   the companion `btcctl` CLI talks JSON-RPC against either.
#   `dropwtxmgr` and `sweepaccount` are two small operational
#   helper binaries that ship inside the `btcwallet` repo:
#
#     dropwtxmgr     Drops the entire `wtxmgr` (wallet
#                    transaction manager) namespace from a
#                    wallet's `wallet.db` file.  Used as a
#                    recovery / re-index step:  delete the
#                    cached transaction store + history, then
#                    let `btcwallet` rebuild it by replaying
#                    the chain.  Optionally drops transaction
#                    labels via `--droplabels`.
#
#     sweepaccount   Iterates every spendable output owned by
#                    an `--sourceacct`, builds a single
#                    consolidating transaction that pays
#                    `--destacct`, signs it via the running
#                    `btcwallet` RPC server, and broadcasts.
#                    Used to consolidate dust / reorganize
#                    wallet structure / migrate accounts.
#
# CLI ARGUMENT GRAMMAR  (verbatim from cmd/dropwtxmgr/main.go
#                       + cmd/sweepaccount/main.go
#                       `opts struct` fields parsed by
#                       jessevdk/go-flags; extracted via
#                       `gh api repos/btcsuite/btcwallet/
#                       contents/cmd/...`)
#
#   dropwtxmgr [OPTIONS]
#
#   Options:
#     -f, --force                    Force removal without
#                                    interactive y/N prompt
#     --db <PATH>                    Path to the wallet
#                                    database file
#                                    [default: `<btcwallet
#                                    appdata>/<network>/
#                                    wallet.db`]
#     --droplabels                   Also drop user-applied
#                                    transaction labels
#     --timeout <DURATION>           Timeout when opening the
#                                    wallet database
#                                    [default: btcwallet's
#                                    DefaultDBTimeout]
#
#   ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ
#
#   sweepaccount [OPTIONS]
#
#   Network selection  (mutually exclusive):
#     --testnet                      Use the test bitcoin
#                                    network (version 3)
#     --simnet                       Use the simulation
#                                    bitcoin network
#     --regtest                      Use the regression
#                                    bitcoin network
#
#   RPC connection:
#     -c, --connect <HOST[:PORT]>    Hostname[:port] of the
#                                    wallet RPC server
#                                    [default: localhost]
#     -u, --rpcuser <USER>           Wallet RPC username
#     --cafile <PATH>                Wallet RPC TLS
#                                    certificate
#                                    [default: `<btcwallet
#                                    appdata>/rpc.cert`]
#
#   Sweep parameters:
#     --feerate <AMOUNT>             Transaction fee per
#                                    kilobyte  (Bitcoin
#                                    amount, e.g. 0.00001)
#                                    [default: btcwallet's
#                                    DefaultRelayFeePerKb]
#     --sourceacct <NAME>            Account to sweep outputs
#                                    from
#                                    [default: imported]
#     --destacct <NAME>              Account to send sweeped
#                                    outputs to
#                                    [default: default]
#     --minconf <N>                  Required confirmations to
#                                    include an output
#                                    [default: 1]
#
#   Standard auto-flags  (go-flags built-in):
#     -h, --help                     Show help
#
# AXIS / CORPUS POSITION
#   Direct dependency on `github.com/btcsuite/btcd` (and
#   sister modules `btcsuite/btcd/btcutil`, `btcsuite/btcd/
#   btcjson`, `btcsuite/btcd/chaincfg/chainhash`, `btcsuite/
#   btcd/rpcclient`, `btcsuite/btcd/txscript`, `btcsuite/
#   btcd/wire`) declared in go.mod ‚Äî `btcsuite/btcd` is THE
#   canonical Go Bitcoin protocol library, maintained by
#   the btcsuite collective at the btcsuite/btcd repository
#   (6,500+ stars; the predominant typed Go Bitcoin
#   wire-protocol / consensus library, originally Conformal
#   Systems' from-scratch reimplementation of Bitcoin Core
#   ‚Äî every major Go Bitcoin / Lightning project depends on
#   it: lightninglabs/lnd (Lightning Network Daemon),
#   lightninglabs/faraday, BoltzExchange/boltz-client,
#   getAlby/nostr-wallet-connect, elnosh/gonuts (Cashu),
#   buildonspark/spark, breez/lspd, anyswap/CrossChain-
#   Bridge, hieblmi/go-host-lnaddr, decred/atomicswap,
#   getAlby/ldk-node-go, and dozens of other production Go
#   Bitcoin applications).  btcsuite/btcd exposes the typed
#   `*wire.MsgTx` / `*wire.MsgBlock` / `*wire.BlockHeader` /
#   `*wire.OutPoint` / `*wire.TxIn` / `*wire.TxOut` /
#   `*wire.TxWitness` / `*wire.MsgInv` / `*wire.MsgGetData` /
#   `*wire.MsgPing` / `*wire.MsgPong` / `*wire.MsgVersion` /
#   `*wire.MsgVerAck` / `*wire.MsgFeeFilter` /
#   `*wire.MsgSendCmpct` / `*wire.MsgCmpctBlock` /
#   `*wire.MsgGetBlockTxn` / `*wire.MsgBlockTxn` /
#   `*wire.MsgMerkleBlock` / `*wire.MsgFilterAdd` /
#   `*wire.MsgFilterClear` / `*wire.MsgFilterLoad`
#   wire-protocol message types, the typed `chainhash.Hash`
#   /  `chainhash.Hash256` (32-byte SHA-256d hash with
#   typed reverse-hex-string formatting), the typed
#   `chaincfg.Params` (with `chaincfg.MainNetParams`,
#   `TestNet3Params`, `TestNet4Params`, `SimNetParams`,
#   `RegressionNetParams` named genesis/halving/network-id
#   constants), the typed `btcutil.Amount` /
#   `btcutil.NewAmount(btc float64)` /
#   `amount.ToBTC()` / `amount.ToUnit(AmountSatoshi)` /
#   `btcutil.MaxSatoshi` / `btcutil.SatoshiPerBitcoin`
#   amount primitives, the typed `btcutil.Address` /
#   `AddressPubKey` / `AddressPubKeyHash` /
#   `AddressScriptHash` / `AddressWitnessPubKeyHash` /
#   `AddressWitnessScriptHash` / `AddressTaproot` /
#   `AddressSegWitV0PubKeyHash` address-type tree, the
#   typed `txscript.NewBuilder()
#   .AddOp(OP_DUP).AddOp(OP_HASH160).AddData(hash)
#   .AddOp(OP_EQUALVERIFY).AddOp(OP_CHECKSIG).Script()`
#   script builder + `txscript.PayToAddrScript(addr)` /
#   `txscript.MultiSigScript(pks, n)` /
#   `txscript.NullDataScript(data)` /
#   `txscript.ExtractPkScriptAddrs(script, params)` /
#   `txscript.NewSigCache(maxEntries)` /
#   `txscript.NewEngine(prevScript, tx, txIdx, flags,
#   sigCache, hashCache, prevOutValue, prevOutFetcher)
#   .Execute()` script execution engine, the typed
#   `txscript.RawTxInWitnessSignature(...)` /
#   `txscript.WitnessSignature(...)` /
#   `txscript.SignatureScript(...)` signature helpers, the
#   typed `btcec.PrivateKey` /  `PublicKey` /  `Signature`
#   /  `KoblitzCurve` /  `S256()` ECDSA / Schnorr primitives,
#   the `rpcclient.New(connCfg, ntfnHandlers)` JSON-RPC
#   client with every typed method
#   (`client.GetBlockHash(height)`,
#   `client.GetBlockHeader(hash)`,
#   `client.GetBlockVerbose(hash)`,
#   `client.GetRawTransaction(txHash)`,
#   `client.SendRawTransaction(tx, allowHighFees)`,
#   `client.EstimateSmartFee(blocks, mode)`,
#   `client.GetBalance(account)`,
#   `client.ListUnspentMin(minconf)`,
#   `client.SignRawTransaction(tx)`, etc.) and an
#   asynchronous notification channel for WebSocket
#   subscribe-style streams, the typed `btcjson.*`
#   request/response schemas for every Bitcoin RPC method,
#   the typed `wire.NewMsgTx(version)
#   .AddTxIn(NewTxIn(prevOutpoint, sigScript, witness))
#   .AddTxOut(NewTxOut(value, pkScript))` transaction
#   builder, and the typed `mempool.*` mempool primitives
#   for full-node mempool acceptance.  `btcwallet` builds
#   on top of btcsuite/btcd's wire / consensus / RPC layers
#   by adding a typed `wallet.Wallet` with the BIP-44 /
#   BIP-49 / BIP-84 hierarchical account model, BIP-39
#   mnemonic seed support, watch-only loading via output
#   descriptors, the `wtxmgr` (wallet transaction manager)
#   on-disk store, the `chain.Client` Bitcoin node
#   interface (chooses between `chain.RPCClient` for
#   btcd-style RPC and `chain.NeutrinoClient` for the
#   lightweight Neutrino BIP-157/158 SPV protocol), and
#   the JSON-RPC wallet-server surface that mirrors
#   Bitcoin Core's wallet RPC.  `dropwtxmgr` and
#   `sweepaccount` are operator-side helper binaries that
#   speak this same wallet stack ‚Äî `dropwtxmgr` opens the
#   `wallet.db` BoltDB file directly through `walletdb.Open`
#   and drops the `wtxmgr` namespace; `sweepaccount`
#   connects to a running `btcwallet`'s RPC via
#   `rpcclient.New` and constructs a sweep transaction
#   through `wallet/txauthor.NewUnsignedTransaction` +
#   `txrules.DefaultRelayFeePerKb` + `txsizes.*` weight
#   estimators.  Verified via:
#     gh api repos/btcsuite/btcwallet/contents/cmd/
#         dropwtxmgr/main.go
#       ‚Üí import "github.com/btcsuite/btcd/btcutil"
#       ‚Üí opts struct: Force / DbPath / DropLabels /
#                        Timeout
#       ‚Üí flags parsed by github.com/jessevdk/go-flags
#     gh api repos/btcsuite/btcwallet/contents/cmd/
#         sweepaccount/main.go
#       ‚Üí import "github.com/btcsuite/btcd/btcjson"
#       ‚Üí import "github.com/btcsuite/btcd/btcutil"
#       ‚Üí import "github.com/btcsuite/btcd/chaincfg/
#                 chainhash"
#       ‚Üí import "github.com/btcsuite/btcd/rpcclient"
#       ‚Üí import "github.com/btcsuite/btcd/txscript"
#       ‚Üí import "github.com/btcsuite/btcd/wire"
#       ‚Üí opts struct: TestNet3 / TestNet4 / SimNet /
#                        RegressionNet / RPCConnect /
#                        RPCUsername / RPCCertificateFile /
